To duplicate an ad set in NewsBreak, you can follow these steps:
1. Navigate to your campaign dashboard.
2. Select the ad set you want to duplicate.
3. Look for the 'Duplicate' option, usually found in the actions menu or toolbar.
4. Click 'Duplicate' and follow any prompts to confirm the duplication.
This will create a copy of your ad set with all its settings, which you can then modify as needed.
If you need more detailed instructions, feel free to check out our Help Center or let me know if you have any other questions!
How to pass cost to redtrack

To pass cost data to RedTrack from NewsBreak, you'll need to set up a postback integration. Here's a brief overview:
1. Go to your NewsBreak ad account and navigate to the Event Management section.
2. Create or test a web event, selecting 'Postback' as your tracking type.
3. Choose 'RedTrack' as your third-party tracking service.
4. Follow the instructions in the Ad Manager to successfully save your event.
For detailed steps, you can refer to this article: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). Let me know if you have any other questions!
What is the Click Cost ID for redtrack

The Click Cost ID for RedTrack is typically a parameter you need to include in your postback URL to track the cost associated with each click. Unfortunately, I don't have the specific Click Cost ID details, but you can find this information in your RedTrack account settings or documentation.
If you're setting up a postback, make sure to check the RedTrack template and instructions provided by NewsBreak for any specific parameters related to cost tracking. If you need further assistance, please reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com.
